[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man seriously assaulted in disturbance

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been seriously assaulted in Aberdeen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident, during which the 29-year-old man received facial injuries, happened in Hill Street at about 19:30 on Sunday.
The area was taped off by police and investigations were also being carried out in South Mount Street.
Police Scotland said they were initially called out to reports of a "disturbance". Officers were said to be following a positive line of inquiry.
